ðŸ“˜ Dynamic Polymorphism (Upcasting)

Animal a = new Dog();

Compiler: checks reference type (Animal)
JVM: executes object type (Dog)

Think of remote control (Animal a) connected to a device (Dog).
Remote can only see buttons on Animal,
Device executes Dog behavior.

How Method Search Happens
COMPILER: Searches in reference type (Super class)
JVM: Executes from object type (Sub class)

Extra Note:
This explains why overriding is runtime polymorphism, while overloading is compile-time polymorphism.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Overloading vs Overriding

| Feature                | Overloading  | Overriding                |
| ---------------------- | ------------ | ------------------------- |
| Type                   | Compile-time | Runtime                   |
| Same class or subclass | Yes          | Subclass only             |
| Parameters             | Must differ  | Must be same              |
| Return Type            | Can differ   | Must be compatible        |
| Static Method          | Allowed      | Not allowed (Hiding only) |

Var-Args Limitation: Only one per method, must be last parameter.

Type Promotion: Char or byte gets promoted automatically if method does not exist for their type.

